	Jobs


	Currently we are hiring for the following positions







Director of Plant Transformation
Taxa is developing the infrastructure which makes it easier, cheaper and faster to genetically engineer plants. We are the team behind Glowing Plant, which was the first ever Kickstarter campaign for a synthetic biology application. Our long term ambition is to develop a 'cloud laboratory' focused on plant synthetic biology in order make genetic engineering of plants available to a broader participant group; we are just beginning to offer that service to partner app developers. This role will help develop and expand our plant transformation capabilities. We work out of a lab in SOMA which is 2 blocks from Caltrain. This is a small startup team so there is significant opportunity to contribute to growth in our capabilities and to define and grow the role.  ResponsibilitiesMain role is to lead and operate our plant transformation facility to generate stable transgenic plant lines, role will include:Managing tissue culture regeneration proceduresPerforming plant transformations (primarily with gene gun)Developing new transient experiment capabilitiesExpanding the range of plant species we can engineerResearching novel transformation systemsParticipating in general lab duties  Ideal backgroundEither MS/PhD in Plant Sciences or 3-4 years experience in plant transformation facilityInterest in biotech startup career / DIY BioFun and friendly with good interpersonal skills  How to applyPlease submit a resume and cover letter (pdf or word) via email to antony at taxa dot com.












 

 



















