	Investors


	Announcements from the TAXA team











 


2016 Annual Report



		4/30/2017
	



		0 Comments
	


 


It’s my pleasure to bring you our first Annual Report. Now that we have a large number of investors, following our successful Title III equity crowd-raise on WeFunder, we will use this report to keep you all updated on the condition of our business and any changes to our business plan as it evolves over time.

In this report you will find an update on our business strategy and plan, information on the Company and capital structure and our 2016 Financial Statements.

We plan to launch Orbella, our fragrant moss product, very soon. The design, packaging and branding work is all complete and we are just figuring out the final issues in manufacturing/production. When we do launch I hope you can help us by tweeting, Facebook sharing and otherwise spreading the launch online. If you have connections to journalists or online distributors now would also be a great time to introduce those to us.

Thank you once again for the trust and faith you have shown by investing in TAXA. It truly is an honor to have your support and I’m continually humbled by the belief you have shown in what we are working on, even more so given that we have not met many of you in person. Without that trust our mission to use biotechnology to create a more sustainable future would just not be possible.

Please don’t hesitate to reach out to me if you have any questions, comments, concerns or interesting ideas to share with us.

Antony Evans



TAXA Biotechnologies 2016 Annual Report by Antony Evans on Scribd









		0 Comments
	


 


TAXA platform launch enables anyone to design novel consumer plants without stepping into a lab



		4/23/2015
	



		0 Comments
	


 

We are excited to announce the launch of the TAXA platform at Synbiobeta.  The TAXA platform has been specifically designed to engineering novel metabolic pathways into plants for the development of new consumer applications without ever needing to step into a lab. We keep costs low using the latest automation technologies and our system allows insertion and optimization of pathways up to ten genes long.   But the best thing is that we make our plants in such a way that we can ship them to customers in the United states free from any regulatory approval process so that developers can sell and distribute them immediately they are ready. This dramatically reduces the cost and time of bringing a product to market, and allows pursuit of an agile product development strategy where bioentrepreneurs release successive versions of a product which improve over time. Working online also means developers can take a product to market no matter the restrictive local regulations on synthetic biology imposed by European bureaucrats.  The TAXA platform has been developed by the team behind the Glowing Plant project, we've taken the infrastructure we built to make the glowing plant brighter and are making it available to other third party app developers.   Our vision is a world where everyone has access to the tools of synthetic biology, where you don't need a phd or millions of dollars in funding to express your creativity and develop a new biological application. We expect that by reducing the barriers to engineering plants we can unleash a wave of creativity and develop hundreds and ultimately thousands of new genetically engineered apps.  For more information please visit http://www.taxa.com Contact  To learn more about this please contact:  Antony Evans, founder & CEO  665 3rd Street, Suite 230, San Francisco, CA 94107 USA Tel: +1-415-779-6333 antony@taxa.com







